column8: Widespread embedded black algae, indicative of failed anti-fouling properties of the paint.
Many areas missing paint in normal areas at the waterline, edges of keel, and rudder
Widespread embedded algae. Gel coat exposed in several areas. Shaft anode to be replaced on next service
Widespread embedded algae. Gel coat exposed in several areas. Bottom in urgent need of painting. Shaft donut anode temporarily installed, streamlined   to be installed on next service.
Replaced both shaft anodes. Paint missing in large areas along waterline and many places on hull. Repainting advised asap.
No obstruction found in galley drain.
